AGI - It's been 55 years since in 1970, a demonstration with 20 million citizens in the square, prompted the United Nations to establish World Earth Day. Today
200 thousand partners in 193 countries actively co-involve more than one billion people each year making
l'Earth Day the most impactful environmental awareness event in the world.&nbsp;>
The celebrations organized by Earth Day Italia and the Focolare Movement are among the best in the world with hundreds of thousands of visitors to the Village for the Land of Villa Borghese in Rome, an event inaugurated in 2016 just while in New York the Paris Climate Agreement was ratified.&nbsp;
These official events:
From 10th to 13th April to the Galoppatoio di Villa Borghese> the historical event of the spring of the Capital will take place to which tens of thousands of students and families from all over Italy will participate. The park of the Biodiversity of the Forest Carabinieri, the Fire Brigades, the Science Village with the most important Italian research bodies, dozens of associations and sports federations with equipped fields and Olympic champions, Children's Village with fun laboratories, and the 17 squares on the objectives of the UN Agenda 2030. A place where everything is strictly free – the organizers emphasize – just as it is free all that Nature gives us every day. The programme can be consulted on www.villaggioperlaterra.it &nbsp;
From 10 to 16 > on the Pincio Terrace 7 days of great feast for the Earth with many attractions starting from a green market with more than 20 artisans. And then talk shows, dance performances, the workshop of international street artist Moby Dick,> and aperitifs at sunset with so much good music together with RDS>, Inna Cantina, Rino Gaetano Band and extraordinary DJs. The famous DJ Emanuele English will celebrate his 30 years of career with a great festival with “tech house” music on the Pincio terrace, Saturday 12 April from 16 to 24.
The colourful March for the Earth, which on the 13th morning at 11:00 am, will depart from the Terrace of Pincio > to reach the Galoppatoio di Villa Borghese, crossing Viale delle Magnolie. The programme can be consulted on www.villaggioperlaterra.it &nbsp;
from 14 to 16 April at the Casa del Cinema> second edition of the Festival IMPATTA DISRUPT.> Three days of work on Innovation > for Sustainable Development in which political, economic, financial decision-makers will discuss the extraordinary Italian potential in the field of Innovation >. There will be 6 major themes addressed by this edition: Digital Transition; Environment Health; Food; Finance; Urban Development. The program can be consulted on www.festivalimpatta.it &nbsp;
<h2>"Dinosaurs in meat and bone"</h2>
<br> Absolute novelty of the 2025 edition collaboration with the Appia Joy Park in Rome and its permanent exhibition “Dinosaur in flesh and bone” with paleo-sculptures of natural-size dinosaurs, curated by paleontologist Simone Maganuco. A real dive in the prehistory that, in an extraordinaryly effective way, will remind the public of the Village for the Earth how much the risk of extinction can be concrete when the ecosystem becomes inhospitable. #OnePeopleOnePlanet - The Multimedia Marathon&nbsp;<br> On the day of 22 April – 55° Earth Day – the final event of the Italian celebrations with a great multimedia marathon created in collaboration with the Rai, which will offer exciting insights on all themes of the 2030 Agenda, with the participation of Artists, Scientists, Journalists and Divulgators. The celebrations will then end at the Fuksas Cloud with the award of the “Reporters for the Earth 2025”> and the “Concert for the Earth” of the TIROMANCINO. >
“Dieci anni fa during an Extraordinary Jubilee Pope Francis inaugurated the Village for the Earth by surprise > and putting aside the speech prepared for the occasion said “you transformed deserts into forests” – said Antonia Head of the Focolare Movement – to &nbsp;ten years from that moment the organizers of the Village for the Earth do not forget its desert prophetic gaze and today more than ever want to illuminate the many little corners of the earth”
“Earth Day – said Pierluigi Sassi president of Earth Day Italia> – is the only time of the year in which billions of people are actively involved in the fight against climate change. An important opportunity to become all aware of the urgency of this crisis and the decisive role that each of us must play at this historic moment. It is no longer the time of sensitization. It is the time of real and concrete change in our everyday lives. It is not from above that the solution will come but from the commitment of all of us”.
